# FINANCIAL DOMAIN RULES

## 1. CONSISTENCY FIRST
- Always prioritize data consistency over convenience
- Never suggest non-transactional shortcuts

---

## 2. TRANSACTION SAFETY
- Clearly define transaction boundaries
- Never mix DB update and external calls without design explanation
- Prefer:
  - Outbox pattern
  - Idempotency

---

## 3. AUDITABILITY
- Ensure all operations are traceable
- Include:
  - timestamp
  - transaction id
  - correlation id

---

## 4. NO SILENT FAILURE
- Always handle errors explicitly
- Never swallow exceptions

---

## 5. DETERMINISTIC DESIGN
- Avoid non-deterministic logic in core flows
